questions.prompt:
A developer wrote the following buggy code:

const itemCount = "5";
const priceEach = 2000;
const total = itemCount * priceEach;
console.log(total);
console.log(itemCount === priceEach);
console.log(itemCount == 5);

(a) Predict the output of each console.log — write your prediction as a comment on each line. (b) Explain in a comment above the first line why itemCount is declared incorrectly. (c) Rewrite the first line to fix the type bug so that total calculates correctly as a number.
